    "title": "Nestle India is Hiring: Quality Control Engineer (Senior)",
    "description": "Nestle India has an exciting opening for a Quality Control Engineer at our Gwalior office. Join a company that values innovation, collaboration, and continuous learning.\n\nAbout Nestle India:\nNestle India is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Monitor equipment performance and coordinate preventive maintenance\n• Oversee daily production operations to meet output targets\n• Maintain accurate production records and prepare daily reports\n• Coordinate with logistics for dispatching finished goods\n• Ensure environmental compliance and waste management\n• Train and supervise shop floor workers and supervisors\n• Coordinate with design and engineering teams on product improvements\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• CA / CMA / CFA certification\n• 12-20 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Project Management\n• Proficiency in Lean Manufacturing\n• Proficiency in Root Cause Analysis\n• Proficiency in SAP MM/PP\n• Proficiency in Statistical Process Control\n• Proficiency in APQP\n• Proficiency in SolidWorks\n• Proficiency in TPM\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Professional development and training programs\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Learning & development budget\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Transportation and conveyance allowance\n• Salary Range: 35 LPA - 70 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Gwalior, Madhya Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Nestle India!",
